Doc treats a mini horse with excessive thirst and a chicken with a paralyzed crop. An emotional support rabbit needs a checkup before heading off to college, and clinic staffer, Hilary, brings in one of her own dogs for veterinary care. .

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol
programme.desc: An ice storm shuts down the clinic and newborn labs are melting hearts. When treacherous weather leaves injured animals in its wake, Dr. Pol and his team slide in to fix busted hips and toe tips. Dr. Lisa handles a demanding delivery while Dr. Brenda impresses by corralling cattle and wrangling racehorses.

programme.title: The Incredible Dr. Pol
programme.desc: Dr. Pol races against the clock to save the life of a mother cow. A whirlwind of emergencies keeps Doc out on nonstop farm calls while his team of vets keep the clinic covered. Dr. Nicole is called to check on a beloved reindeer. Dr. Lisa removes a suspicious growth from a sheep dog and Dr. Brenda treats a puppy that is losing weight.

programme.title: Africa's Wild Side
programme.desc: All life is shaped by one powerful driving force: the need to breed. Every animal on the African plains is a player in the mating game. .

programme.title: Africa's Wild Side
programme.desc: There is no tougher place to bring up baby than in the wilds of Botswana. Every parent will do what they can to give their young a fighting chance. .

programme.title: Africa's Wild Side
programme.desc: Botswana is a land of epic beauty, where the wildlife itself shapes the land. Every animal builds, maintains and renovates their structures. .

programme.title: Land Of The Iberian Lynx
programme.desc: Sierra Morena is a mountain range of climatic extremes. The harsh winter puts the lynxes of the Jandula River Valley to the test. Golden eagles, otters, wild boars and cormorants struggle to survive in the land of the Iberian lynx.

programme.title: Land Of The Iberian Lynx
programme.desc: Spring rains bring new opportunities and hope to the land of the Iberian lynx. But for the female lynxes of the valley, it is always a challenge to raise their cubs. The series follows the lynxes in their struggle for survival, from the thrill of the hunt to the tender moments of parenting, and also witnesses their coexistence with other animals like majestic golden eagles or powerful deer.

programme.title: Freaks And Creeps
programme.desc: Lucy Cooke is on a one-woman mission to show why the ugly, weird and overlooked animals of the world can be cute, cuddly and deserving of attention. Join her as she heads off to the rainforests of Borneo. Borneo is its own very unique crucible of weirdness - with countless strange creatures that can only be found there. Lucy's goal is get up close with the giant-nosed proboscis monkey to figure out why this creature looks so strange.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China
programme.desc: Meet China's most affectionate and vocal monkeys in the remote, seasonal forests of Central China. Follow the journey of a baby Golden snub-nosed monkey during the first year of her life as she learns all about her forest home and battles the elements to survive.

programme.title: Madagascar: Legends Of Lemur Island
programme.desc: Millions of years ago, hundreds of castaway creatures crash-landed on Madagascar's rugged shores. Isolated from the mainland, evolution went into overdrive. Of almost a quarter of a million species found on the island, approximately 70 percent are unique.
